THE NEIGHBORHOOD:
Peaceful, shaded, residential Sullivan`s Gulch. Ten minute walk to Lloyd center/MAX. Under ten minutes to Fred Meyer. Few blocks south of the restaurants/shops/bars of Broadway. Buses: #70, #8, #77 a few blocks away, #19, #20, #12 not too far. Great for non drivers like me, but conveniently off the Banfield for drivers.
THE SPACE:
Available is the quite big larger room in a two bed, one bath apartment. On the second floor, accessed by covered stairs, there`s a nice view of the neighborhood foliage. You also get two closets and half the basement storage. BRING YOUR FURNISHINGS! I just have a few, generally mismatched things for living, dining rooms, and kitchen.
Apartment complex built in 1960s but kept in repair. Coin Washer and dryer on premises (in basement with external access).
Cats ok per landlord ($200 deposit) but not really looking to take on pets.
Car port available!
ME: gay male, Mid-thirties, stably employed (ten years at same company), Semi-sporty (gym, hiking, sometimes soccer), with mostly old-timey tastes (classic movies/music , opera, art museum). Prefers books to video games, fondness for travel and eating out, good cheap food. Drinks in moderation, omnivorous, with no allergies.
LOOKING FOR:
Stable, low-drama, trustworthy, relaxed but responsible roommate. Friendly and pleasant enough to chat a bit, communicative enough to get the needs of the apartment done, but respectful of personal things and private time. Stable/verifiable employment, pays bills on time, pitches in to help keep place clean. Smoke/drug/420 free.
I MUST STRESS: the pleasant, peaceful nature of the neighborhood. Other tenants are young but not partiers. No one`s loud, sound may carry between apartments but interior is well insulated. HOWEVER, being off the I-26, the freeway creates white noise. Windows are double glazed and trees provide some sound block in summer.
I treat the apartment as personal space for downtime and relaxation, not really a social space. I myself rarely entertain, a few people would be ok, but not a crowd.
THE OFFER:
Monthly: $520 rent + split utilities (approx $40 wifi + approx $25 electric)
Lease is month to month with 30 day notice to move, but if we`re a good fit, looking for someone to stay a while (I`ve already been here 2 ½ years, and some neighbors up to a decade). Rent rarely increases.
UP FRONT COSTS:
Credit/criminal background check: $30
Security: $200
First month`s rent
Application with proof of income (payroll doc, bank statements)

If you`ll be here on vacation, here for work but want a homier setting, or are just looking for a place to land while relocating, we`re in a great location. It`s a private, cozy, charming, garden setting in the thick of our urban hustle and bustle! A perfect mix of quiet and serenity at home--a great setting for creative types--and lively, interesting places to eat, play and shop nearby.
We`re creative types ourselves, working (sometimes in the front, main house, and occasionally out of town) in TV, film, eco-friendly apparel, and home renovation, and have hosted TV and screenwriters, filmmakers, composers, actors, music producers, opera singers, chefs, urban farming planners, costume designers, internet gurus, a language translator, physicians, lawyers, professors, journalists and photographers.
We`d love to know a bit about you, and what brings you to the area, and would be happy to tell you more about us, answer any questions you have about the property or the area, and can provide a list of references, too. Thanks for checking out our cottage, and best of luck finding the perfect spot for your LA visit!
RATES:
The garden cottage is available for:
$175/night
$1,200/week
$2,695/month
...for single occupancy (1 person) (and for an additional $10/night for each additional person),
Includes utilities, furnishings, housewares and linens.

7/18/14-8/1/14 (Arriving no sooner than 4pm, Departing no later than 11am)
9/1/14 and beyond

www.flickr.com/photos/22608935@N07/sets/72157603662103320/
THE COTTAGE:
• Cozy yet light and airy, detached private guest cottage with lots of windows, looking out to greenery from every room (approx. 660 sq ft + deck/porches for total approx. 750 sq ft)
• Large bedroom (12`x13`) with walk-in closet (3`x5`) -- To be furnished with queen-sized bed or larger...tbd (most likely it will be a California King bed) (see notes below)
• Living room (11`x18`) w/French doors leading to private rear sundeck (8`x13`), lawn, pebble patio, trees & room to garden or read in the sun in your own small private backyard (50` wide x 15` deep, from the house to the creeping fig-covered wall and trellis)
• Arched-entry dining area (8`x7`) with original built-in cabinetry and view of hills
• Converted sun-filled tiny screened-in porch (5`x6`) off kitchen -- Great for breakfast for one, a mini office, as storage, or even as litterbox room! (We will probably furnish as a writer`s nook, with a small table and chair that can easily be removed)
• Hardwood and tile floors, and great moldings throughout
• Tiled kitchen (8`x10`) with refrigerator, vintage stove, microwave and douglas fir wood floors
• Tiled bathroom (5`x9`) with original deep tub beneath private window with woodsy view
• Your own washer and dryer
• A/C window unit and gas wall heater
• Feels very light and airy, and very private even though the yard in front is shared with front main house
• Utilities included (Including power, water, gas, wifi, trash, gardener). Depending on length of stay, premium cable may be available. No landline phone is provided.
• Fully furnished, including equipped kitchen, housewares and linens -- Just bring your suitcase and groceries!
• Continental breakfast available upon request. Ask us more about this!
• Will consider pets with additional pet deposit -- see below. Yard may have the occasional well-behaved cat or dog visiting with their owners as guests in our front main house.
• We prefer non-smokers. All smoking is permitted outside only.
THE PROPERTY:
• Secure, key-entry gated property / Up about 40 steps
• Ample non-restrictive street parking on quiet street, usually within 4-5 driveways of our driveway. There are no parking time limitations (other than the city-wide 72 hr limit) nor "street cleaning" days, and no residential parking permits are required.
• Front house is rented out on a similar basis, and/or owner-occupied (+ 1-2 quiet roommates, typically 30/40-somethings. We are early 40s creative professionals + happy baby! ...some/all of whom are sometimes out of town with family or for work)
• Large shared yard (50`x50`) in between your cottage and our main front house (where we live and sometimes rent out up to two of our four bedrooms--see our other listing on Airbnb). Yard has a lawn, rose garden with pebble path, fruit trees (lemon, white sapote, kumquat and fig), brick patio, firepit (we sometimes have a stash of firewood!), weber gas bbq, hammock, tree house and vegetable and herb garden (vegetable garden and grapevines are a bit dormant this time of year, though!). Depending on the season and weather, our homemade ping pong table, boules, croquet or badminton sets might be set up on the lawn and are ready for your use! The entire back yard and all of your cottage and private back yard are fenced in, on our 8,000 sq ft lot. Also consider yourself forewarned of the occasional skunk, raccoon or opossum (we even had two coyote sightings) come dusk!
LOCATION:
• The cottage is nestled, hilltop, behind our front main house, up about 40 stairs. We`re in a wonderful, quiet, hilly neighborhood, north of Sunset Blvd. on the border of Echo Park and Silver Lake.

Silver Lake is central to Hollywood/Burbank/Glendale studios. Various buses stop at the nearby Sunset Bl. and Coronado St. intersection. Our "walk score" is 85, "Very Walkable"!...but don`t forget to account for the fairly steep hills you have to climb and descend if you`ll shop for heavy groceries on foot!
